availableChallenges.title: Unlock the island
availableChallenges.description:
Wait for the game master to provide a KEY to unlock the rest of the island.

Enter this key in the flag section and click submit.

availableChallenges.title: The French Connection
availableChallenges.description:
Now let's learn how to modify our code to return the French version of this FLAG. The base64 version of our FLAG is: `RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5`.

You have to decrypt this base64 variable and return your flag in your webservice to get it. Here is the code you will need. Modify the "hello" function with this code:

```python import base64 base64_string = "RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5" flag = base64.b64decode(base64_string).decode('utf-8') return FLAG ```
Then restart your container to see the result.

availableChallenges.title: Unlock the island
availableChallenges.description:
Wait for the game master to provide a KEY to unlock the rest of the island.

Enter this key in the flag section and click submit.

availableChallenges.title: The French Connection
availableChallenges.description:
Now let's learn how to modify our code to return the French version of this FLAG. The base64 version of our FLAG is: `RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5`.

You have to decrypt this base64 variable and return your flag in your webservice to get it. Here is the code you will need. Modify the "hello" function with this code:

```python import base64 base64_string = "RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5" flag = base64.b64decode(base64_string).decode('utf-8') return FLAG ```
Then restart your container to see the result.

Now let's learn how to modify our code to return the French version of this FLAG. The base64 version of our FLAG is: `RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5`.

You have to decrypt this base64 variable and return your flag in your webservice to get it. Here is the code you will need. Modify the "hello" function with this code:

```python import base64 base64_string = "RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5" flag = base64.b64decode(base64_string).decode('utf-8') return FLAG ```
Then restart your container to see the result.

Now let's learn how to modify our code to return the French version of this FLAG. The base64 version of our FLAG is: `RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5`.

You have to decrypt this base64 variable and return your flag in your webservice to get it. Here is the code you will need. Modify the "hello" function with this code:

```python import base64 base64_string = "RkxBR19CT05KT1VSXzk5" flag = base64.b64decode(base64_string).decode('utf-8') return FLAG ```
Then restart your container to see the result.
